   "source": [
    "# Generating a global grid"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ebd13c5d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "This tutorial will demonstrate the generation of a global grid in spherical coordinates"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "152b0bf9",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import meshkernel\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "fba95942",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "mk = meshkernel.MeshKernel(projection=meshkernel.ProjectionType.SPHERICAL)\n",
    "mk.mesh2d_make_global(num_longitude_nodes=192, num_latitude_nodes=100)\n",
    "mesh2d = mk.mesh2d_get()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "e1ab1314",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Plot the result"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "1099478a",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 2000x1000 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plt.close(\"all\")\n",
    "figsize = (20, 10)\n",
    "mesh2d = mk.mesh2d_get()\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=figsize)\n",
    "mesh2d.plot_edges(ax, color=\"k\")"
   ]
  }
 ],
